This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the mathematical analysis of learning dynamics in deep neural networks. It also involves the acquisition, organization, and deployment of abstract knowledge, which are key topics in machine learning. 

The paper also touches on natural language processing and semantic cognition, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

The use of neural networks and the analysis of their dynamics also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The paper's focus on abstract knowledge and its acquisition could also place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's potential applications in computer vision, particularly in the analysis of neural representations, could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
